OL,3,CPolice officers who fail vetting to be
OL,4,Cautomatically sacked under new rules
OL,6,FThe move follows criticism from
OL,7,FMetropolitan Police Commissioner Sir
OL,8,FMark Rowley, who accused officials of
OL,9,Fdragging their feet over giving police
OL,10,Fchiefs stronger powers to sack rogue
OL,11,Fofficers.
OL,13,FHe previously said it is "absurd" that
OL,14,Fofficers who are not fit to hold
OL,15,Fvetting cannot be lawfully sacked.
