OL,3,CPolice officers who fail vetting to be
OL,4,Cautomatically sacked under new rules
OL,6,FRowley said: "The ability to hold a
OL,7,Fvetting clearance is the most basic
OL,8,Findication of whether someone can be
OL,9,Ftrusted to hold the extensive and
OL,10,Foften intrusive powers that police
OL,11,Fofficers are given. It was never right
OL,12,Fthat an officer could lose their
OL,13,Fvetting, but not lose their job.
OL,15,F"These reforms close that glaring gap
OL,16,Fin the law and will allow us to move
OL,17,Fswiftly to remove those who have no
OL,18,Fplace in policing.
