OL,3,CPolice officers who fail vetting to be
OL,4,Cautomatically sacked under new rules
OL,6,F"This matters not just for the public
OL,7,Fwe serve but for the vast majority of
OL,8,Fhardworking officers who should be
OL,9,Fable to feel safe, have full trust in
OL,10,Fthose they work alongside and have the
OL,11,Fconfidence of the public."
OL,13,FThe Home Office said the changes come
OL,14,Fin response to recent legal cases that
OL,15,F"brought to light" the difficulty
OL,16,Fforces face in removing officers unfit
OL,17,Fto protect the public.
