OL,3,CPolice officers who fail vetting to be
OL,4,Cautomatically sacked under new rules
OL,6,FThe Home Office also plans to
OL,7,Fintroduce further safeguards to
OL,8,Fimprove vetting national standards
OL,9,Flater this year, including stronger
OL,10,Frequirements to suspend officers under
OL,11,Finvestigation for violence against
OL,12,Fwomen and girls.
OL,14,FOfficers convicted of certain criminal
OL,15,Foffences will also be automatically
OL,16,Ffound guilty of gross misconduct.
OL,18,FWhile there are existing processes for
OL,19,Fforces to deal with allegations of
OL,20,Fmisconduct, failing vetting may not be
OL,21,Fenough to sack officers.
